{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Mechanical remediation pass (non-design findings) applied to S2/S4/S5. Highlights:\n\n- **REJECTED as invalid — S2 BLOCK T1** (\"`/rebase:chain` is not a real Gerrit endpoint\"). Verified against the Gerrit REST API docs: `POST /changes/{change-id}/rebase:chain` DOES exist (3.6+, so the 3.14.1 instance has it) — the review's own advisory T3 concedes this. Kept the endpoint; wrote the precise path. The fact-check DID surface a real fix: the RebaseInput field is **`rebase_on_behalf_of_uploader`**, not `on_behalf_of_uploader`.\n- **S2:** per-member SHA tracking (`tested_shas{}`) + all-members-fresh-Verified rule for chains (R5 safety); `re_drive_count` + `paused` added to the schema/phase enum; ancestor-atomic submit = `POST /changes/{tip}/submit`; chain FFO check = bottom-most member's parent == main tip; FIFO field = `ApprovalInfo.date` via `o=DETAILED_LABELS`; bounded Verified-await; Submit-ACL + impersonation-capability + credential preconditions (xref S5); named `infra/autolander/loop.py`; testing AC.\n- **S4:** heartbeat checked BEFORE setting `Autosubmit` (no orphaned label) + heartbeat-read-failure → `lander_down`; `o=DETAILED_LABELS` for vote reads; ALL exit codes pinned (`4 not_requested`, `7 error`, `75 pending`); land-status fallback-precedence + never-requested behavior; JSON schema added to `docs/land-contract.md`; named `infra/autolander/land.py`; testing AC.\n- **S5:** declared the external state volume + `compose-up.sh SITE_SUBDIRS` edit (incident-2731 drift gate); factual fix — container `unhealthy` is a Docker event, not a journald line (probe via `docker inspect`); HEALTHCHECK probes the LOCAL heartbeat (never Gerrit, avoids flap); `ssm.tf` for_each + `AUTOLANDER_GERRIT_TOKEN` into shared `.env`; All-Projects `[capability]` provisioning named; bounded SIGTERM drain; scope reconciled (service-lifecycle wiring vs core loop); E2E proving step + testing AC.\n\nREMAINING: 7 genuine design decisions surfaced to the reviewer one at a time (heartbeat form; park/hand-back protocol + S2/S3 boundary; CloudWatch histogram transport; unhealthy→restart mechanism; land Gerrit-client reuse; agent credential injection; queue-status transport + emergency-stop sentinel form). Not decided unilaterally."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783792351747944001,"uuid":"2dd10ebe-0d23-4476-bfcc-fc3d0f984fef"}